---
// seam-diagram — Chapter 070 Lesson 1, "One seam, many channels".
//
// The lesson's spine, made spatial: call sites fire ONE event; the dispatcher
// owns every channel decision. The figure reads left→right.
//
//   Call site ──dispatch(event)──▶ Dispatcher ──┬──▶ Email (Resend)
//   (Server Action / webhook)                   └──▶ In-app inbox (notifications)
//        │
//        └──(violet, NOT through the dispatcher)──▶ audit_logs (operator-facing)
//
// The audit arrow leaves the SAME call-site box (not the dispatcher) and is a
// distinct violet to mark it as a separate path / separate audience. The
// audit_logs box sits low under the call site so the violet arrow runs straight
// down the far-left margin and never crosses the fan-out arrows on the right.
//
// Inside the Dispatcher box, a compact strip of four muted chips previews the
// internal pipeline (registry lookup → preference read → dedup check → fan-out)
// that later lessons build — kept visually subordinate, not explained here.
//
// Built with <ArrowDiagram> (LeaderLine) because the boxes are two-line custom
// HTML (a monospace title + a muted under-label) plus the dispatcher's internal
// chip strip, and the per-arrow semantic coloring (the violet audit path) is the
// whole point — D2/Mermaid plain-label boxes wouldn't carry it. The arrows are
// positioned from document.body, so the wrapping <Figure> MUST be
// expandable={false}: relocating the body into the lightbox breaks the lines.
//
// Chrome is theme-aware (Starlight gray/white vars flip light/dark). The audit
// accent (#7c3aed violet) is used as-is in both themes — a mid-tone that reads on
// either background. A margin:0 reset on every node defeats Starlight's injected
// prose margins inside the figure.

import Figure from '../../../figures/Figure.astro';
import ArrowDiagram from '../../../figures/ArrowDiagram.astro';

// The four chips of the dispatcher's internal pipeline, in order. Subordinate to
// the boxes — a preview of what later lessons build, not a thing explained here.
const pipeline = [
	'registry lookup',
	'preference read',
	'dedup check',
	'fan-out',
];

const AUDIT_VIOLET = '#7c3aed'; // violet-600 — the separate, operator-facing path

const arrows = [
	// The one event in: call site → dispatcher. The labeled main wire.
	{
		from: 'seam-callsite',
		to: 'seam-dispatcher',
		label: 'dispatch(event)',
		startSocket: 'right',
		endSocket: 'left',
		startSocketGravity: [70, 0],
		endSocketGravity: [-70, 0],
		labelOffset: [0, -26],
	},
	// Fan-out #1: dispatcher → Email. Lands on the TOP channel box.
	{
		from: 'seam-dispatcher',
		to: 'seam-email',
		startSocket: 'right',
		endSocket: 'left',
		startSocketGravity: [80, -30],
		endSocketGravity: [-60, 0],
	},
	// Fan-out #2: dispatcher → In-app inbox. Lands on the BOTTOM channel box.
	{
		from: 'seam-dispatcher',
		to: 'seam-inbox',
		startSocket: 'right',
		endSocket: 'left',
		startSocketGravity: [80, 30],
		endSocketGravity: [-60, 0],
	},
	// The separate path: call site → audit_logs, straight DOWN the far-left margin.
	// Violet, and deliberately NOT routed through the dispatcher. Stays clear of the
	// fan-out region on the right.
	{
		from: 'seam-callsite',
		to: 'seam-audit',
		label: 'direct write',
		color: AUDIT_VIOLET,
		startSocket: 'bottom',
		endSocket: 'top',
		startSocketGravity: [0, 50],
		endSocketGravity: [0, -50],
		labelOffset: [0, 0],
	},
];
---

<Figure expandable={false}>
	<ArrowDiagram arrows={arrows}>
		<div class="seam not-content">
			{/* ── Column 1: the one source, with audit_logs low beneath it ── */}
			<div class="seam-col seam-col-source">
				<div class="seam-box" id="seam-callsite">
					<span class="seam-title">Call site</span>
					<span class="seam-under">Server Action / webhook</span>
				</div>
				<div class="seam-box seam-box-audit" id="seam-audit">
					<span class="seam-title">audit_logs</span>
					<span class="seam-under">operator-facing</span>
				</div>
			</div>

			{/* ── Column 2: the dispatcher — the only place channels are known ── */}
			<div class="seam-col seam-col-mid">
				<div class="seam-box seam-box-dispatcher" id="seam-dispatcher">
					<span class="seam-title">Dispatcher</span>
					<span class="seam-under">lib/notifications/</span>
					<div class="seam-pipeline" aria-hidden="true">
						{
							pipeline.map((chip, i) => (
								<>
									{i > 0 && <span class="seam-chev">›</span>}
									<span class="seam-chip">{chip}</span>
								</>
							))
						}
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			{/* ── Column 3: the channels the dispatcher fans out to ── */}
			<div class="seam-col seam-col-channels">
				<div class="seam-box" id="seam-email">
					<span class="seam-title">Email</span>
					<span class="seam-under">Resend</span>
				</div>
				<div class="seam-box" id="seam-inbox">
					<span class="seam-title">In-app inbox</span>
					<span class="seam-under">notifications table</span>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</ArrowDiagram>
	<Fragment slot="caption">
		The dispatcher is the only place that knows about channels — the call site
		fires one event and never imports Resend or touches the notifications table.
		Operator-facing <strong>audit logs</strong> are a separate write the caller
		makes directly, because they're a different audience entirely.
	</Fragment>
</Figure>

<style>
	.seam {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: nowrap;
		align-items: flex-start;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 96px;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 16px 6px;
		font-family:
			ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
	}

	.seam-col {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		margin: 0;
		flex: 0 1 auto;
	}

	/* Column 1: call site at top, audit_logs pushed low so the violet arrow runs
	   straight down the far-left margin, clear of the fan-out. */
	.seam-col-source {
		align-items: stretch;
		gap: 86px;
	}

	.seam-col-mid {
		justify-content: center;
		align-self: center;
	}

	/* Column 3: the two channel boxes stacked, centered on the dispatcher. */
	.seam-col-channels {
		align-items: stretch;
		align-self: center;
		gap: 22px;
	}

	.seam-box {
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 3px;
		padding: 11px 16px;
		border-radius: 10px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, transparent);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* The dispatcher is the focal box — a touch heavier border so the eye lands
	   on it as the seam. */
	.seam-box-dispatcher {
		border-color: var(--sl-color-gray-4, #94a3b8);
		border-width: 2px;
		padding: 12px 18px 11px;
	}

	/* audit_logs: dashed + violet-tinted to read as the separate operator path. */
	.seam-box-audit {
		border-style: dashed;
		border-color: color-mix(in srgb, #7c3aed 55%, var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1));
	}
	.seam-box-audit .seam-title {
		color: #7c3aed;
	}

	.seam-title {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.86rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.2;
		white-space: nowrap;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.seam-under {
		font-size: 0.66rem;
		line-height: 1.2;
		white-space: nowrap;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* The internal pipeline strip — subordinate: small, muted, single row. */
	.seam-pipeline {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: nowrap;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 4px;
		margin: 8px 0 0;
	}

	.seam-chip {
		padding: 2px 7px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: var(--sl-color-gray-6, #f1f5f9);
		font-size: 0.58rem;
		line-height: 1.2;
		white-space: nowrap;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.seam-chev {
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		line-height: 1;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-4, #94a3b8);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* Narrow viewports: stack the three columns. The right→left sockets degrade to
	   vertical arcs between stacked boxes — readable, and the labels still float in
	   the gaps. The pipeline chips wrap to two rows if needed. */
	@media (max-width: 760px) {
		.seam {
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: center;
			gap: 52px;
		}
		.seam-col {
			width: 100%;
			align-items: center;
		}
		.seam-col-source {
			gap: 52px;
		}
		.seam-box {
			width: min(18rem, 100%);
		}
		.seam-pipeline {
			flex-wrap: wrap;
			justify-content: center;
		}
	}
</style>
